snippet.textDisplay:
I am a local popular singer in Tn & I get it. I'm in no way at his level nor genre. I'm old school Janis Joplin/stevie Nicks- ish. I have a small circle world wide & i get it.
I just started just to honor both my dad's last wishes when they passed from cancer 2 yrs ago & it's gotten bigger than I expected. It moves fast. It will get away from you & the fandom desperation is difficult & painful, sometimes terrifying.

To be honest his pain seems to be getting deeper almost on a path of self destruct. Im worried.
His words are raw truth. People NEED to gear his message.
Others have no idea how hard it is to be a musician. Seriously.
I have to deal with sabotage during shows. I have had stalkers attack us, threaten my children & slash our tires & I'M NOBODY!!
I do charities & benefits. Family friendly, church & my music is southern rock inspirational & fun. It's a crazy world & getting worse daily. People rarely open their windows anymore let alone putting yourself out there exposed and vulnerable with a big target on your chest.
People want to be us. They want it so bad some will kill to keep others like us from rising. Even the small town nobodies like me. Hell I've seen people stabbed over a $100 bowling alley karaoke contest.

I cant imagine the level of pain. Heartbreak & evil that runs across his path daily. His guts are spread out on every stage. Hes chopping up & handing out tiny pieces of his soul & some are spitting in his face.

I LOVE Tom McDonald only rapper I will listen to. He speaks to me & that says a lot. I'm just a 51 yr old rockin mom in Tennessee.
Hes preaching the truth. Press on Tom God Bless
